                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 437.00/49.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Cuban Congress adjourned March 26 without acting on the Guantanamo matter.
                    New Congress convenes April 6.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Note.</hi>—The proposed treaty expired by limitation
                        June 27, 1913, since by its article 5 a stipulation was made for its
                        ratification within six months from its date: December 27, 1912. See <ref
                            target="frus1912#pg_297">For. Rel. 1912, p. 297</ref>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
